# Physics Education Patterns

## Mathematical Content Rendering

### KaTeX Integration
Use [src/components/MathMarkdown.tsx](mdc:src/components/MathMarkdown.tsx) for all mathematical content:

```typescript
import MathMarkdown from '@/components/MathMarkdown'

// Render physics equations
<MathMarkdown content="The kinetic energy formula is \\( KE = \\frac{1}{2}mv^2 \\)" />

// Display math blocks
<MathMarkdown content="\\[ F = ma \\]" />
```

### Math Syntax Standards
- Inline math: `\\( E = mc^2 \\)`
- Display math: `\\[ F = ma \\]`
- Common physics symbols: `\\vec{v}`, `\\Delta x`, `\\theta`
- Units: Use proper spacing `\\text{m/s}^2`

## Question Types Architecture

### Question Type Definitions
Reference [src/types/assignment.ts](mdc:src/types/assignment.ts) for all question types:

```typescript
// Multiple Choice
interface MultipleChoiceQuestion extends BaseQuestion {
  type: 'multiple-choice'
  options: string[]
  correctAnswer: number
  explanation?: string
}

// Numerical Answer
interface NumericalQuestion extends BaseQuestion {
  type: 'numerical'
  correctValue: number
  tolerance?: number
  unit?: string
  unitOptions?: string[]
}
```

### Physics Calculation Integration
Use [src/utils/physics-calculator.ts](mdc:src/utils/physics-calculator.ts) for automatic answer generation:

```typescript
import { calculatePhysicsSolution } from '@/utils/physics-calculator'

const solution = calculatePhysicsSolution(questionText)
if (solution) {
  setCorrectValue(solution.value)
  setUnit(solution.unit)
}
```

## Curriculum Organization

### Physics Units Structure
Follow [src/data/physics-units.ts](mdc:src/data/physics-units.ts) for curriculum organization:

```typescript
export const physicsUnits = {
  'unit-1': {
    title: 'Motion in One Dimension',
    lessons: {
      'lesson-1-1': { title: 'Position and Displacement' },
      'lesson-1-2': { title: 'Velocity and Speed' }
    }
  }
}
```

### Topic Tagging
Use consistent physics concept tags:
- Kinematics: `['velocity', 'acceleration', 'displacement']`
- Forces: `['newton-laws', 'friction', 'tension']`
- Energy: `['kinetic-energy', 'potential-energy', 'conservation']`

## AI-Generated Content

### Question Generation Prompts
Structure physics-specific prompts:

```typescript
const prompt = `
Generate a physics question about ${topic}.

Requirements:
- Grade level: ${gradeLevel}
- Difficulty: ${difficulty}
- Include relevant physics principles
- Provide step-by-step solution
- Include common misconceptions as distractors

Physics Context:
- Units: Use SI units
- Significant figures: Appropriate for level
- Real-world applications: ${context}
`
```

### Scenario Image Generation
Use physics-appropriate image generation:

```typescript
const imagePrompt = `
Create a clear physics diagram showing:
- ${physicsScenario}
- Label key components
- Use standard physics conventions
- Simple, educational style
- Black and white line drawing
`
```

## Grading and Assessment

### Rubric Standards
Create physics-specific rubrics:

```typescript
const physicsRubric: RubricCriterion[] = [
  {
    name: 'Physics Concepts',
    description: 'Understanding of relevant physics principles',
    maxPoints: 4,
    levels: [
      { score: 4, description: 'Demonstrates complete understanding' },
      { score: 3, description: 'Shows good understanding with minor gaps' },
      { score: 2, description: 'Partial understanding with some misconceptions' },
      { score: 1, description: 'Limited understanding' },
      { score: 0, description: 'No evidence of understanding' }
    ]
  }
]
```

### Auto-Grading Patterns
For numerical answers:

```typescript
const isCorrect = Math.abs(studentAnswer - correctValue) <= tolerance
const partialCredit = Math.max(0, 1 - Math.abs(studentAnswer - correctValue) / correctValue)
```

## Student Progress Tracking

### Activity Tracking
Use [src/contexts/StudentActivityContext.tsx](mdc:src/contexts/StudentActivityContext.tsx) for progress monitoring:

```typescript
const { trackActivity } = useStudentActivity()

// Track lesson engagement
trackActivity({
  type: 'lesson_view',
  lesson_id: lessonId,
  duration: timeSpent
})

// Track assignment progress
trackActivity({
  type: 'assignment_progress',
  assignment_id: assignmentId,
  question_id: questionId,
  correct: isCorrect
})
```

## Accessibility for Physics Content

### Screen Reader Support
```typescript
// Provide alt text for physics diagrams
<img 
  src={scenarioImage} 
  alt="Physics diagram showing a block on an inclined plane with forces labeled"
  className="physics-diagram"
/>

// Use proper headings for problem structure
<h3>Given Information</h3>
<h3>Find</h3>
<h3>Solution</h3>
```

### Mathematical Accessibility
```typescript
// Provide text alternatives for equations
<span aria-label="Force equals mass times acceleration">
  <MathMarkdown content="\\[ F = ma \\]" />
</span>
```

